# Weapons & Projectiles System

Read `docs/Weapons_Projectiles_Spec.md` before making any changes.

## Core Design Decisions
- Three archetypes: ballistic (hull damage), energy (shield damage), missiles (balanced, requires shield strip)
- Heat tracked **per hardpoint** — not per ship
- Power tracked **per ship** — shared pool, energy weapons compete with shield regen
- Four hardpoint types: fixed, gimbal, partial turret, full turret (different fire arcs)
- Hardpoints are **damageable components** with their own HP and degraded states
- Projectile pool split: C# dumb pool (bullets/pulses) + GDScript guided pool (missiles)
- Lasers: continuous beam (hitscan, held fire) AND rapid pulse (discrete shots)
- Missile guidance mode is a JSON property: `track_cursor`, `auto_lock`, `click_lock`

## PerformanceMonitor Metrics (use exactly these strings)
- `ProjectileManager.dumb_update` — C# dumb projectile tick
- `ProjectileManager.guided_update` — GDScript guided projectile tick
- `ProjectileManager.collision_checks` — all collision resolution
- `ProjectileManager.active_count` — set_count each frame
- `HitDetection.component_resolve` — damage application to components

## Data Files
- `data/weapons.json` — all weapon stats (damage, fire rate, heat, power cost, etc.)
- `data/damage_types.json` — damage type effectiveness matrix

## Watch Out For
- ProjectileManager.cs is the ONLY C# file in the project — everything else is GDScript
- Projectiles inherit parent ship velocity at spawn (see physics spec)
- Never hardcode damage values — they come from JSON
- Hardpoint degradation affects accuracy/fire rate before full destruction
- Energy weapons draw from the ship power pool — check for power starvation edge cases
